Big Mac is
inconveniently late.

112
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:10,700
<i>(panting)</i>

113
00:06:10,820 --> 00:06:11,880
Well, there you are!

114
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,960
Have I not told you
about punctuality?

115
00:06:14,410 --> 00:06:16,350
Ah! I don't want
to hear it!

116
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:19,770
<i>♪ (pitch pipe tone) </i>

117
00:06:20,340 --> 00:06:24,380
<i>♪ (no doo wop introduction) </i>

118
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:25,390
(gulp)

119
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:31,320
Big Mac! Can you please
start the song?

120
00:06:33,070 --> 00:06:34,190
Nnope.

121
00:06:34,470 --> 00:06:35,110
Big Mac!

122
00:06:35,470 --> 00:06:36,560
Did you lose your voice?

123
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:37,200
<i>(gulp)</i>

124
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,430
Eeyup.

125
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:40,980
<i>(gasps)</i>

126
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,720
♪

127
00:06:44,730 --> 00:06:47,130
Whatever did you
do to cause this?

128
00:06:47,450 --> 00:06:48,790
Well...

129
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,910
Howdy, everypony!

130
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:55,270
And welcome to the 12th Annual
Ponyville Turkey Call!

131
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,310
<i>(cheering)</i>

132
00:06:57,330 --> 00:06:58,620
<i>(gobble)</i>

133
00:06:59,070 --> 00:07:00,450
Who will take the
title this year?

134
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:02,000
Will it be somepony new?

135
00:07:02,220 --> 00:07:05,460
Or will the Turkey Call
champion of six years

136
00:07:05,470 --> 00:07:09,420
<i>defend his title to make</i>
<i>it lucky number seven?</i>

137
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:12,460
We'll find out if
ya stop yer gabbin'

138
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:14,780
and git on with
the gobblin'!

139
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,250
All right, everypony!

140
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,950
Let's talk turkey!

141
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,200
Big Mac, yer up!

142
00:07:21,110 --> 00:07:22,190
<i>(takes a deep breath)</i>

143
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,720
A Turkey Call?

144
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:30,320
You lost your voice
doing a...Turkey Call?

145
00:07:30,690 --> 00:07:32,700
Lost his voice and the title!

146
00:07:32,790 --> 00:07:33,900
<i>(Pinkie gobble)</i>

147
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:37,440
Now we can't
perform tonight.

148
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,470
Wait! What? No!

149
00:07:41,030 --> 00:07:42,120
You have to perform!

150
00:07:42,330 --> 00:07:44,750
Otherwise the fundraiser
will be a disaster.

151
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:47,590
Well, we cannot perform
tonight with only three voices.

152
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:48,830
Why not?

153
00:07:49,130 --> 00:07:51,230
It would take rearranging
all the music

154
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:52,420
and we just don't have time.

155
00:07:52,690 --> 00:07:54,820
<i>I'm sorry, Fluttershy,</i>
<i>but I have no remedy</i>

156
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:55,840
<i>for this situation.</i>

157
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:57,070
<i>(gasp)</i>

158
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,720
Of course!

159
00:07:58,940 --> 00:07:59,750
A remedy!

160
00:08:00,030 --> 00:08:00,810
Follow me!

161
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:09,990
<i>(hoarse) Ahhhh!</i>

162
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:10,940
Hmmm.

163
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:13,080
Aaahh.

164
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:17,580
I can cure this
pony that is hoarse,

165
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:20,450
but it will take
a longer course.

166
00:08:20,990 --> 00:08:21,720
Come again?

167
00:08:22,010 --> 00:08:22,590
Hmmm.

168
00:08:22,950 --> 00:08:25,420
I can mix a brew that
will work just right,

169
00:08:26,020 --> 00:08:28,590
